{
  "texts": [
    "QLoRA (Quantized Low-Rank Adapter) utilizes this approach to facilitate efficient fine-tuning of LLMs on limited hardware.",
    "By employing 4-bit NormalFloat (NF4), an optimized data type for normally distributed weights, and double quantization, which further reduces memory usage by quantizing the quantization constants, QLoRA drastically cuts down the memory needed without sacrificing performance (48).",
    "Figure 4 Training curves of Llama3 8B fine-tuning using QLoRA on domain-specific data (freeways crash studies)",
    "After fine-tuning the Llama3 8B model using QLoRA on a dataset incorporating 226 research studies, it has become more familiar with crash studies on freeways, the contributing factors, and the influence of these factors.",
    "The fine-tuned Llama3 will be employed to identify the main causes of crashes."
  ]
}